{
  "stem": "95.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the seven-story-high apartment house was filled with lots of children, and it was joyous.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Most of the people who lived in the apartment-- most men and women-- were religious Jews, which means they worked to Friday, and then Saturday, they're not working.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "On Sunday, they go to work.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In the ghetto in Paris, in the Fourth Arrondissement-- Paris was made with 20 sections.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We call them arrondissements.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In the Fourth Arrondissement, where I lived, there was a very famous ghetto, [FRENCH].",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they had a school there, an elementary school for-- separately for young ladies and for young men.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And there, even though we were taught by non-Jews-- all our teachers were non-Jews, and we were taught in French-- [BACKGROUND NOISE] and because of that, our parents sent us to this school so we will be off on Saturdays and Sundays and have all the Jewish holidays off, too.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we kids were thrilled, because not only did we have the Jewish holidays off, but also the Catholic and the non-Jews holidays off.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it was thrilling.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Really, it was great, until I was 12 years old.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I graduated this elementary school there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But what was fantastic in our apartment house-- this Madame Alfin not only didn't care if we pay the rent-- and I'm sure some of the families could not afford it and didn't pay-- but she hired social workers to take care of us children when we came back from school from 4:00 PM to 7:00 PM.",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "There was a-- we called it a locale on the first floor, two huge rooms where the kids will go there to do their homework, and then be taken care of by these social workers, who were remarkable ladies.",
      "word_count": 39
    }
  ],
